sp.p:
If a Peece be diſcharged with the waight of his Bullet in Serpentine powder, and afterwards diſcharged with halfe the waight of his Bullet in ſuch Corne powder as ſhall cauſe the Peece to caſt the ſame ground;
No. 
I demand if the ſame Peece be againe Charged with halfe the quantity of either ſort, whether theſe Ranges ſhall alſo bee equall? The forme of Charging being vniforme, and temper of the Peece alike.
